Implemented only the requested **“Resting Potential from a Charge Wall”** section changes.

**What changed**
- [src/pages/resting_two_ion_common.ts](/Users/mq20185996/Dropbox/crossleylab/code/electrochemical_signals_progression_web/src/pages/resting_two_ion_common.ts)
  - Removed the **Prediction Prompt** card from the UI.
  - Renamed visible ion terminology to **Na+ / K+** (controls, status labels, legend, trace fallback text, equation text).
  - Reordered classroom controls to:
    1. Particles  
    2. Diffusion SD  
    3. Electric strength  
    4. NA+ permeability  
    5. K+ permeability  
    6. NA+/K+ pump strength
  - Added **`NA+/K+ pump strength`** as a **numeric input** (`type="number"`), not a slider.
  - Added pump behavior in the sim step loop (strength-scaled 3 Na+ out / 2 K+ in transport bias).

- [src/pages/inspect_resting_potential_charge_wall.ts](/Users/mq20185996/Dropbox/crossleylab/code/electrochemical_signals_progression_web/src/pages/inspect_resting_potential_charge_wall.ts)
  - Updated page copy from Ion A/B wording to Na+/K+ wording.
  - Removed/rewrote prediction-association phrasing in description/hints to align with request.

